modules.description: Provides functions to generate map implementations based on key types, including insertion, lookup, and iteration. Works with standard data types such as int, string, and bool. Enables quick creation of maps for configuration settings or data indexing.

Converts key-value expressions into map data structures using AST manipulation, extracts and processes sequences of expressions for mapping, and constructs module expressions from identifiers or inferred types. Works with OCaml's AST nodes, location data, and expression descriptions to build and format map literals. Used to generate efficient, type-safe maps from syntactic constructs in code transformation pipelines.
